          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "K-12",
          "Performance on Next Question",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect ( 0)",
          "3275 students",
          "Mathematics-related topics in an ITS",
          "In-Question activities, \nQuestion scores",
          "[In-Question Activities]",
          "Most KT approaches only consider answers to model learner knowledge without considering how they got to the answer, which provides a naive and incomplete picture of a learner’s knowledge.  ",
          "Model proposed is an expansion of DKT that considers the clickstream of the in-question activities as an integral part of the knowledge model. ",
          "Answer states are stored in JSON.\n\nAll data is normalized and, if necessary, One-Hot Encoded. \n\nTimestamps are converted to time intervals (in logathmic form) and each partial score is considered as categorical. \n\nData is used tp build an embedding representation using an Autoencoder.",
          "Clickstream Knowledge Tracing-PT, CKT-FT, CKT-E2E, DKT",
          "3 Repeated-Holdout Method",
          "Math Unit:\n\n{AUC: 0.8313 - CKT-FT, }\n\nQuestion ID:\n\nMath Dimension:",
          "CKT is presented under 3 paradigms:\n\nFrozen Pre-trained weights - CKT-PT\n\nFine-tuned rpe-trained weights - CKT-FT\n\nTrained from Scratch - CKT-E2E\n\nAuthors experiment their results based on 3 forms of indexing for knowledge components:\n\n1. At the Question ID level, \n\n2. At the Math Unit, \n\n3. At the Math Dimension\n\nAuthors also identify what is the minimum number of questions a learner needs to answer to address the cold-start problem and find that CKT-PT reequires between 5-8% less questions than DKT.",
          "Comparison to DKT only, discarding other potential approaches."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
